      "role": "user",
      "content": "i'm a bit confused though. if the text \"the right of the people to keep and bear arms, shall not be infringed\" is what they wrote, how is prioritizing that text \"activism\"? isn't it actually the opposite—just following what's written on the page instead of trying to guess what everyone was thinking in the 1700s? wouldn't you say the \"militia\" argument is more of a stretch than just reading the words literally?",
